# statistics
MEAN - 1+4+23+143/5
sum of all values / total numberof values
MODE - number that is repeated the most number of times
MEDIAN - middle value
if even digits - 10, 20, 30, 40
median is 20+30/2 =25

VARIANCE - how far data values are dispersed from MEAN
STANDARD VARIATION - used to calculate amount of dispersion
SD CALCULATION-
Step 1: Find the mean.
Step 2: Subtract the mean from each score.
Step 3: Square each deviation.
Step 4: Add the squared deviations.
Step 5: Divide the sum by the number of scores. Average of squared value - VARIANCE
Step 6: Take the square root of the result from Step 5.  - this is SD
